name: Celtic Peat Picture Frame
description:
Measuring 8” X 6” X 0.5” (20cm X 15cm X 1.5cm) 
Boxed weight 500 grams

The Ancient Celts are famous for their carvings, art and design. The Book of Kells is arguably the finest example of Ancient Celtic Art in existence

This Hand Crafted design encompasses the interlocking Trinity Knot-work associated with this famous manuscript

This Frame is suitable for photo’s measuring 6” X 4”  or
(15cm X 10cm) in portrait or landscape format

name: Bog Oak Peat Picture Frame
description:
Measuring 9” X 7” X 0.5” or (23cm X 18cm X 1.5cm) 
Boxed weight 850 grams

Bog Oak is ancient timber which has decayed and been preserved  in boglands over thousands of years

This CraftyPeat interpretation is a representation of this material in peat and further inspiration taken from animals in Celtic Mythology. The Raven is represented here which in for Celtic Warriors symbolised protection

This Frame is suitable for photo’s measuring 6” X 4”  or
(15cm X 10cm) in portrait or landscape format

name: Claddagh Peat Picture Frame
description:
Measuring 12” X 10” X 0.5” or (30 cm X 25 cm X 1.5cm) 
Boxed weight 1400 grams

This is the famous Claddagh  design characterised by interlocking knot-work consisting of three different parts-The Heart (for love), The Crown (for Loyalty) and the hands (for friendship). 

These have come to denote pride in Irish heritage while continuing to be symbols of love or marriage 

This Frame is suitable for photo’s measuring 7.5” X 6” or
 (19 cm X 14.5 cm) in portrait
